<div id="subtree-container" class="subtree-container"><div class="aea2d7dde423afa7ad9351a0886150a8-scss b51b00c1669ad99a1c607cd1e77c2824-scss" style="inset: 306px 269px 0px 0px; justify-content: flex-end;"><div class="afeebf1df237d4103108ba40799802d6-scss"><div class="c13443431e58facf06f9d12490b92a82-scss" style="width: 90vw; max-width: 8.5in;"><div class="_0df5ec6b9902d7d22ccfa3ebb4f35211-scss">Successful Information Management</div><div class="e5e059a27f4c194020f0d961a3cb5989-scss" dir="auto"><div class="fr-view"><p>A successful project requires a smart plan, lean scope, collaborative processes, team agreement, supporting technology, and solid tracking, control, and verification workflows.</p>
<p>Our project execution planning ensures that all parties are clearly aware of the opportunities and responsibilities associated with the incorporation of Building Information Modeling (BIM) into our project.&nbsp;</p>
<p>Our plan details the correct processes for executing BIM throughout the project's lifecycle.</p>
<p>On this project, we will follow these four steps to ensure that all teams are meeting the project's Exchange Information Requirements:</p>
<p><span style="font-family: Open sans,sans-serif;"><img src="https://private.lodplanner.com/projects/4104/plan-content/1603349099387_c873e3ee-d4ff-4bc3-b4d0-78cb3fa1a793.png?Expires=1768815902&amp;Signature=aojaBs29r9u6RK6VXOK1M7wJfAeuXOfUG6RNpD8xVgQpd7nEwWus4AiFhZkHRWiwFlqc1DzAUbgbQfjWL4rQNk2hEeDLFwxlBE1daWnUI3Xb9S9zmV4-VzUyBroKrXo9jnBOYfmSUFn9007DYEq~MZhXa-ToOycU1xFs26O9jo3jXLVrheSn3g~oItmpN9nJp9xwIy7kRK8sjIA2jKu72eDBR2~Iqzuh3sSGsKND6uEKkZ1tW8ALTjWjXn4p2zdsUjJKb1qiUrb77QnPdIt8S7DG9D8nAgFiPY5bRjECr~xaDhJjy74b4avi-hPcymu7ZVJC1nWxzVaUM9PH6fEWBQ__&amp;Key-Pair-Id=APKAJRIVA6WNZT4BZJPQ" style="width: 963px;" class="fr-fic fr-dib"></span></p>
<ol>
<li>Identify high value Model/BIM Uses that will support Exchange Information Requirements&nbsp;</li>
<li>Design and document optimal project execution processes</li>
<li>Define the BIM deliverables in the form of information exchanges</li>
<li>Develop the infrastructure in the form of contracts, communication procedures, technology and quality control to support the implementation</li>
</ol>
<p>To gain the maximum benefits from our BIM implementation, once the <strong>Plan</strong> and <strong>Scope</strong> have been defined and appointed,&nbsp;the Task Teams will <strong>Schedule</strong> their own tasks,&nbsp;our team will <strong>Track</strong> the progress of assigned tasks and <strong>Verify</strong> task completeness <strong>before sharing the model for the described use case.</strong></p></div></div></div></div></div></div>